[{"id":"VR781864","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Which of the following expressions represents the final gravitational potential energy of the three-sphere system?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR781864_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Three spheres, with masses indicated in the figure, are initially far away from each other, and the gravitational potential energy of the three-sphere system is zero. The spheres are then brought together until each sphere is a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"r\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"r\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>r</mi></math></span></span> from the other two, as shown.</p>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">&nbsp;</p>\n\n<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"passage\">\n<div class=\"prose style:1\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows three spheres placed at the vertices of an equilateral triangle with a side length of r. Two of the spheres, each with mass m, form a horizontal base. The third sphere, which has mass 2 m, is located at the top vertex.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR781864.g01.svg\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction negative G times m squared, over r\"><math alttext=\"the fraction negative G times m squared, over r\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>−</mo><mi>G</mi><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mi>r</mi></mfrac></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction negative 2 G m squared, over r\"><math alttext=\"the fraction negative 2 G m squared, over r\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>G</mi><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mi>r</mi></mfrac></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction negative 4 G m squared, over r\"><math alttext=\"the fraction negative 4 G m squared, over r\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>G</mi><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mi>r</mi></mfrac></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the fraction negative 5 G m squared, over r\"><math alttext=\"the fraction negative 5 G m squared, over r\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>5</mn><mi>G</mi><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mi>r</mi></mfrac></mstyle></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":3}]